target: ui
validations:
  - name: hud_elements
    type: agent_validation
    severity: error
    args:
      rubric: >
        Verify the HUD bar displays all required elements: current money balance
        (with gold color), net income per tick (green if positive, red if negative),
        animal count, visitor count, elapsed time (MM:SS format), speed buttons
        (1x, 2x, 3x with the active speed highlighted), and a pause button. When
        the bankruptcy timer is active, a red warning must appear on the HUD showing
        the remaining seconds. The HUD must span the full canvas width at 40px height.

  - name: sidebar_tabs
    type: agent_validation
    severity: error
    args:
      rubric: >
        Verify the sidebar has exactly 3 tabs: Build, Shop, and Research. Clicking a
        tab switches the content panel. The active tab must be visually distinct from
        inactive tabs (different background color). The Build tab must list all 5 biome
        types as buttons with their names and costs. Buttons for biomes the player
        cannot afford must appear disabled (grayed out).

  - name: toast_notification_system
    type: agent_validation
    severity: warning
    args:
      rubric: >
        Verify toast notifications appear for game events (animal born, animal died,
        research complete, etc.). Toasts must slide in from above with an animation,
        hold for approximately 3 seconds, then fade out. Multiple toasts must stack
        vertically without overlapping. A maximum of 5 toasts should be visible at
        once. Expired toasts must be removed from the state.

  - name: info_bar_selection
    type: agent_validation
    severity: error
    args:
      rubric: >
        Verify the info bar at the bottom of the viewport shows details for the
        selected entity. For animals: species name with nickname, happiness percentage
        with visual bar, hunger percentage, health percentage with visual bar, and
        a "(SICK)" indicator in red if applicable. For enclosures: biome name, level,
        animal count/capacity, condition percentage with visual bar, and repair cost.
        When nothing is selected, show a placeholder hint text.

  - name: button_hit_testing
    type: agent_validation
    severity: error
    args:
      rubric: >
        Verify all UI buttons (sidebar tabs, build buttons, speed buttons, pause button,
        menu buttons) respond to clicks within their exact pixel bounds. A click at
        coordinates (x, y) must be tested against each button's {bx, by, bw, bh}
        rectangle. Clicks outside all buttons must fall through to map interaction.
        The hit-test function must account for the canvas CSS scaling (clientX/Y vs
        canvas logical coordinates).
